	<bf:mainTitle>Library of Congress archives, Central File series</bf:mainTitle>
      </bf:VariantTitle>
    </bf:title>
    <bf:collectionArrangement>
      <bf:CollectionArrangement>
	<bf:collectionOrganization>Arranged in six series. Series 1: John Russell Young, 1897-1899; Series 2: Herbert Putnam and Archibald MacLeish, 1895-1947; Series 3: Archibald MacLeish and Luther Harris Evans, 1896-1955; Series 4: Herbert Putnam-Archibald MacLeish Index; Series 5: Archibald MacLeish-Luther Harris Evans Name Index; and Series 6: National Security Classified Information.</bf:collectionOrganization>
      </bf:CollectionArrangement>
    </bf:collectionArrangement>
    <bf:summary>
      <bf:Summary>
	<rdfs:label>Administrative files consisting of correspondence, memoranda, reports, notes, forms, dockets, cross references, printed matter, and other records of the Library of Congress Office of the Librarian during the tenures of four Librarians of Congress: John Russell Young, 1897-1899; Herbert Putnam, 1899-1939; Archibald MacLeish, 1939-1944; and Luther Harris Evans, 1945-1953. Includes a Herbert Putnam and Archibald MacLeish Index containing cross reference information for individual correspondents, private companies, organizations, and government offices, as well as a subject index and collection index; and a Archibald MacLeish and Luther Harris Evans Index containing cross reference information for individual correspondents, private companies, organizations, and government offices.</rdfs:label>
      </bf:Summary>
    </bf:summary>
    <bf:note>
      <bf:Note>
	<rdf:type rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/mnotetype/lang"/>
	<rdfs:label>Collection material in English.</rdfs:label>
      </bf:Note>
    </bf:note>
